<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
{{> head head-title=title.about head-description=meta-description.about head-link=links.about }}
<body>
  <div id="content-wrapper">
    <header>
      <nav id="header" class="navbar navbar-default navbar-static-top" role="navigation">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="navbar-header">
            <button class="navbar-toggle collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".navbar-collapse">
              <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            </button>
            <a class="navbar-brand active" href="{{links.index}}" data-event-category="navigation-menu" data-event-action="home">{{meta-author}}</a>
          </div>
          <div class="collapse navbar-collapse">
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav navbar-right">
              <li class="active"><a href="{{links.about}}">about</a></li>
              <li><a href="{{links.blog}}">blog</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </header>
    <section id="page-content">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>{{title.about}}</h1>
        <p>
          My name is Brian and I'm a developer at GoDaddy in the hosting department. I joined as a C++ engineer back in 2008 and I’ve helped create an automation layer around our dedicated hosting, VPS, and shared hosting (cPanel and Plesk) products. I’ve also done a fairly large amount of UI development, working on our Hosting Control Center.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before GoDaddy, I was in the manufacturing (TMG) organization at Intel (2005 – 2008). I worked on middleware products (COM/DCOM, guaranteed delivery services, etc) used at the D1D factory in Hillsboro, Oregon. D1D is/was the flagship factory where the ground-breaking process engineering took place for processors. Products I worked on were used in the 1264 (65nm), 1266 (45nm) and 1268 (32nm) processes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before Intel and GoDaddy, I also worked for several small businesses in the payment processing industry.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some friends and I formed Morgopolis Studios, LLC in 2012 and released our first video game, <a href="http://bit.ly/1ou4jUa">Magicians &amp; Looters</a>, for the Xbox 360 Indie Games marketplace. It’s also available <a href="http://bit.ly/234nDdJ">for PC on Steam</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          I’ve been writing software since the early 1990s (when I was 10 or 11 years old) and I still love it. I attended and got a bachelors from UAT (University of Advancing Technology) here in the valley (Tempe, AZ).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="container">
        <div id="email-form">
          <h2 id="contact">{{title.contact}}</h2>
          <p>
            Do you have a question or comment? Let me know what you think. Be sure to include your email address if you want a response.
          </p>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="email-name">Name (optional)</label>
            <input id="email-name" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Your name" data-event-category="contact-me" data-event-action="name">
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="email-address">Email address (optional)</label>
            <input id="email-address" type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Your email address" data-event-category="contact-me" data-event-action="email">
          </div>
          <div class="form-group intentionally-blank">
            <label for="email-url">Url</label>
            <input id="email-url" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Your website url" data-event-category="contact-me" data-event-action="url">
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="email-message">Message</label>
            <textarea id="email-message" class="form-control" rows="5" placeholder="Your message" data-event-category="contact-me" data-event-action="message"></textarea>
          </div>
          <button id="email-submit" type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="submitEmailForm();" data-event-category="contact-me" data-event-action="submit">
            Submit <i class="loading-button" style="display:none;"></i>
          </button>
        </div>
        <div id="email-sent" style="display:none;">
          <h2>Your message has been sent</h2>
          <p>Thanks for the feedback! If you included your email and are expecting a response, I should be able to reply within 24 hours (no promises though).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  {{> footer about=true }}
</body>
</html>